Class TagValuesAsList

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.util.data.AbstractTagValuesReadable
      • com.camerontec.catalys.util.data.AbstractTagValues
        • com.camerontec.catalys.util.data.TagValuesAsList
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IBindable<ListIterator<ITagValue>>, IFIXBytesImportable, ITagValueIterableFromTag<ListIterator<ITagValue>>, ITagValueIteratorBindable<ListIterator<ITagValue>>, ITagValues, ITagValuesReadable, FIXBytesImportable, Serializable, Cloneable, Iterable<ITagValue>

    public class TagValuesAsList
extends AbstractTagValues
    ITagValues implemented as an ArrayList.

    This implementation inherits the performance characteristics of the underlying ArrayList in most cases except for operations where retrieval of a field by tag is required. (gets and removes). In these cases an O(N) search of the list for the matching tag is required before the call to the underlying ArrayList can be made.

      • clearTagValuesBase

        protected void clearTagValuesBase()
        Description copied from class: AbstractTagValues
        The default implementation just calls AbstractTagValuesReadable.getTagValues() and calls AbstractTagValues.removeField(int) for the tag associated with each element in the returned array.

        It is likely that you may want to override this with a more efficient method that has knowledge about the details of the class's implementation.
